# Secrets Setup Guide (Example)

**DO NOT COMMIT THE REAL VERSION OF THIS FILE**

Copy this file to `SECRETS_SETUP.md` (gitignored) and fill in your actual values.

## Doppler Configuration

Doppler is configured at the **bare repository root** so all worktrees inherit automatically.

```bash
# One-time setup at bare repo root (run from ~/git/terraform-proxmox, NOT from a worktree)
cd ~/git/terraform-proxmox
doppler setup --project YOUR_PROJECT_NAME --config YOUR_CONFIG_NAME
```

New worktrees will automatically inherit this configuration - no additional setup required.

## aws-vault Profile

```bash
# The aws-vault profile name for S3 backend access
# Check available profiles: aws-vault list
AWS_VAULT_PROFILE="your-profile-name"
```

## Complete Command Pattern

```bash
# Full command with all credentials
nix develop ~/git/nix-config/main/shells/terraform --command bash -c "aws-vault exec YOUR_PROFILE -- doppler run --name-transformer tf-var -- terragrunt <COMMAND>"
```

## Quick Reference

Replace placeholders:
- `YOUR_PROJECT_NAME` - Your Doppler project
- `YOUR_CONFIG_NAME` - Your Doppler config (e.g., dev, stg, prd)
- `YOUR_PROFILE` - Your aws-vault profile name
